<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-65-0779 </DOCNO><TEXT>Marketing cogeneration will require a different approach than marketinggas, with an imaginative and well-reasoned strategy necessary for success.Part of the reason for the demise of the railroad industry was the inabilityof railroad management to think of their business not as running a railroad,but as providing transportation. Likewise, the single most importantissue the pipeline faces when entering the cogeneration market is dowe want to sell gas or do we want to be in the energy business? Thischapter examines how this issue and others will shape the marketing strategy.It discusses industrial marketing and segmentation, i.e., selection ofcustomer groups that are likely to respond in a similar manner to a marketingstrategy.</TEXT></DOC>